<SLUG> BC-ADONE-LA-DAILYNEWS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MEDIA FIRM JOINS IN AD SITE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ The parent of the &UR;  &LR; Los Angeles Daily News and other Los
Angeles Newspaper Group newspapers led a consortium of media
companies Monday that bought AdOne Classified Network Inc. to
create the nation's largest locally based Web site for classified
advertising.
</P>
<P>
   Denver-based MediaNews Group Inc. already owned a 25 percent
stake in AdOne and the deal, reached Wednesday, creates a privately
held company that will be called AdOne L.L.C.
</P>
<P>
   AdOne and its Web site, classifiedwarehouse.com, will be
co-owned by E.W. Scripps Co., Advance Publications Inc., Donrey
Media Group, Hearst Corp. and Garden State Newspapers, an affiliate
of MediaNews. The ownership group includes four of the 10 largest
U.S. newspaper companies. Terms were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Classifiedwarehouse.com is the Internet's most comprehensive
collection of classified advertising. The ads _ which will come
from the chain's newspapers _ will be distributed on Lycos Inc.'s
main Web site, lycos.com.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have long been believers in AdOne's classified network. But
with the new support of our strategic partners and the provision of
a significant amount of new content on the network, AdOne will be
clearly positioned as the premier provider of online classified
advertising content,'' said William Dean Singleton, president and
chief executive officer of MediaNews Group.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our first and foremost responsibility is to our local
classified advertising customers and our local newspapers have
served their needs well for decades. Now, in addition to
distribution in our local newspapers, our customers will benefit
significantly from the strength of the AdOne network through the
tremendous distribution capabilities of AdOne's ... consumer
site,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Classifiedwarehouse.com's searchable advertising database
averages more than 3 million new ads per month and is expected to
grow to more than 6 million ads by the summer, said Dan Manco,
AdOne's marketing director.
</P>
<P>
   Consumers who can't find a product or service through their
local paper's Web site will be able to conduct a broader search via
classifiedwarehouse.com, he said.
</P>
<P>
   MediaNews Group is the seventh-largest newspaper company in the
United States. It manages newspaper companies with combined daily
and Sunday circulation of approximately 1.55 million and 1.68
million, respectively. In addition to the Daily News, its Los
Angeles-area holdings include the Long Beach Press Telegram, San
Gabriel Valley Tribune, Pasadena Star-News and Whittier Daily News.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &UR;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
