 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, January 27, 1999 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ The chairmen of the Democratic and Republican
national committees have now dutifully denounced this noxious
Council of Conservative Citizens. The declarations of anathema are
somehow a bit pallid, but I suppose their decorum is preferable to
having the chairmen throw up on camera, although that would get the
matter just about right. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for
Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ MIAMI _ By Monday, the Super Bowl will be
over. And we natives finally will be able to erase the forced
hospitality smiles from our faces, get through a traffic light in
less than three changes and know of a hotel that doesn't have a
four-day minimum stay. (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist for Cox
News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ My cerebral approach to
potty-training my son was a little odd, but I liked the
nonconfrontational method. Maybe my way worked better than the
``naked and $75'' technique. Kristofor reassures me that he is
functioning normally and seldom has the urge to suck his thumb or
rob a bank. That's good enough for me. (Elizabeth Schuett, Cox News
Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ At the Really Big Fishing Event for
Really Special People, bringing home a trophy, or frying-pan
fodder, was way down the list of prizes. Close to 1,000 disabled
people fished, while 525 volunteers helped. The fisherpersons came
from as far away as Tyler and Georgetown for the special moments
this event provides. The idea was hatched 11 years ago as a lone
fishing tank in the corner of a room. Now it's an extravaganza with
karaoke, dancing, a photo studio with a grab-bag of disguises, and
food, food, food. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
