 &HT;    With MILITARY-SPENDING. For release Sunday, Jan. 31.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   THE UPS AND DOWNS OF MILITARY SPENDING
</P>
<P>
   Department of Defense spending in billions of constant 1999
dollars:
</P>
<P>
   1945: $504
</P>
<P>
   1950: $132
</P>
<P>
   1955: $250
</P>
<P>
   1960: $267
</P>
<P>
   1965: $288
</P>
<P>
   1970: $334
</P>
<P>
   1975: $258
</P>
<P>
   1980: $282
</P>
<P>
   1985: $418
</P>
<P>
   1990: $365
</P>
<P>
   1995: $278
</P>
<P>
   2000: $280 (estimated)
</P>
<P>
   Source: Department of Defense comptroller and House Armed
Services Commitee
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
