<SLUG> BC-MEANS-CORRECTIVE-HNS </SLUG>
  
 Tuesday, Jan. 26, 1999     
 Editors:   Newspapers that used the MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) filed
Monday, Jan. 25, may wish to use the following corrective:
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The Tuesday column by Marianne Means carried an
error in the 12th paragraph. It should have said that retired Sen.
Dale Bumpers, D-Ark., who defended President Clinton in his
impeachment trial, has been a friend of Clinton for a quarter
century, not a quarter decade.
</P>
<P>
   Hearst News Service\Washington.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
