<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-26 13:44 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8885 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRAVEL-COLUMN-BOS &LR;      01-26 0305
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-COLUMN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STAR LODGINGS AND RESTAURANTS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY MORRIS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   One of the best guides to accommodations and restaurants, the
Mobil Guides, has announced winners of its annual five- and
four-star awards.
</P>
<P>
   This year, there are six first-time five-star awards and 38
repeat recipients. There are also 372 four-star winners. Among
longtime five-star winners are the Broadmoor in Colorado, 39 years;
The Greenbrier in White Sulphur Springs, Va., 38 years; and The
Carlyle in New York, 31 years. The only New England five-star
winners are Twin Farms in Woodstock, Vt., and the Mayflower Inn in
Washington, Conn. Both are for lodging.
</P>
<P>
   New England four-star winners: In Connecticut, Inn at National
Hall in Westport, Jean-Louis restaurant in Greenwich. In Maine, Bar
Harbor Hotel and Bluenose Inn in Bar Harbor; Lodge at Moosehead
Lake in Greenville; Captain Lord Mansion and the Inn at Harbor Head
in Kennebunkport; and the White Barn restaurant in Kennebunkport.
In Massachusetts, Boston Harbor Hotel, the Eliot, Four Seasons
Boston, and The Ritz-Carlton, all in Boston; Wequassett Inn in
Chatham; Blantyre in Lenox; and the Wauwinet on Nantucket.
Massachusetts restaurants: Aujourd'hui at the Four Seasons, Biba,
Hamersley's Bistro, and L'Espalier, all in Boston; Chillingsworth
in Brewster; and Blantyre and Wheatleigh in Lenox. In New
Hampshire: the Balsams in Dixville Notch. In Vermont: Governor's in
Ludlow, Rabbit Hill in St. Johnsbury, Topnotch at Stowe in Stowe,
Woodstock Inn in Woodstock, and Hemingway's restaurant in
Killington.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Samoa information
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Samoa, a South Pacific paradise, now has a Seattle tourist
office. For information on Samoa's 3,000-year-old Polynesian
culture call 425-688-8511.
</P>
</TEXT>
