</P>
<P>
   Senator Joseph Lieberman, in a speech that summed up the mood of
the party, called Clinton's actions ``wrong and unacceptable.''
</P>
<P>
   So what has changed now? Not the president's offenses; Democrats
still admit that these cannot be defended. Not the sense of
