</P>
<P>
   Without the rotten behavior of the president's enemies, it is a
reasonable bet that his party would not be displaying such loyalty
towards him. And if the conduct of the trial, against expectation,
becomes more neutral rather than more partisan, some of that
wafer-thin fidelity may begin to tear.
</P>
<P>
   Democrats are also aware that, by supporting the president, they
are reflecting the public mood. The American people have been
unwavering: all year, by two-thirds majorities, they have wanted to
keep this president in office. They approve of the job he is doing.
</P>
<P>
   For as long as it has existed, the job-performance poll has
always been linked to the state of the economy. Inevitably, when
