   AGL_SETTLE _ ATLANTA _Atlanta Gas Light is expected to jettison
its controversial new rate structure in a settlement with the PSC
that will include $14 million in refunds to 200,000 overcharged
consumers and a return to billing based on actual gas consumption.
(Quinn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TURNER-INTRANET _Turner Broadcasting executives are wielding the
Internet as a scalpel, shaving business expenses while cutting new
paths to reach its 10,000 employees in Atlanta and worldwide.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MCI-INTERNET _ MCI WorldCom this week has trotted out a new
service that lets business customers fine-tune their
telecommunications services using the Internet. The new feature,
its sales and marketing, all come out of Atlanta. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   COKE-EARNINGS _ Coca-Cola reports earnings of 24 cents a share
in the fourth quarter, in line with the warning the company issued
in December. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GAPAC-EARNINGS _ Georgia-Pacific Group reports a profit instead
of a loss that Wall Street had expected, while its Timber Group
beat the forecast by 1 cent per share. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-COLUMN _ Weekly column on how organizations are handling
their Y2K-bug issues, focusing on companies and governments in
Atlanta and the Southeast. (Chambers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ DRIPs _ dividend reinvestment plans _ have been
unbeatable bargains for small-time stock buyers like you and me for
years. Many of them still are. But some companies are doing the
all-American thing: tacking on new services and raising their fees.
You may or may not want the services, but you can't avoid the fees.
(Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0122 -- Its brash big brother, the F-150, may get
the hype and media attention, but the Ford Ranger pickup quietly
continues to stretch its utility with a four-door option that's
definitely on the cutting edge. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
