</P>
<P>
   HKN-ORR-BURE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ There's no mistaking the
emotion in Bobby Orr's voice, even through a telephone line.
Whether he's talking about his admiration for new Florida Panther
Pavel Bure, his fond memories of playing junior hockey or his
opposition to those who say hockey has become too violent, the
former NHL superstar and Tequesta resident speaks with joyous
passion about his favorite game. (Tays, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PEPPER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Dottie Pepper, who recently
moved to Jupiter, Fla., is the LPGA's version of Mr. October _
saving her A game for the Solheim Cup. She has won 14 LPGA events
(but none since 1996), was Player of the Year in 1992 and is sixth
in career earnings ($4.51 million). But she has earned greater
notoriety in recent years for her emotional _ and sometimes
controversial _ play in the Solheim. (Palm Beach Post). MOVED.
</P>
