   COLOMBIA-QUAKE (Armenia, Colombia) _ Earthquake kills at least
1,000 people, authorities say. Dead in provincial capital alone
could reach 2,000. By Richard Chacon. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-HUSSEIN (Amman, Jordan) _ Leaving his nation less than a
week after his return from cancer treatment, King Hussein puts a
successor in charge. By Charles M. Sennott. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-YELTSIN (Moscow) _ President Boris Yeltsin clashes with
his prime minister for the first time, issuing a hospital bed
rebuke for a proposed political truce that would include a check on
his enormous power. By David Filipov. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMPEACHMENT (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) -- House impeachment prosecutors
demand that Monica Lewinsky and two others be subpoenaed, ask
Senate jury to request President Clinton to testify under oath. By
Bob Hohler. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-BLUMENTHAL (Washington) -- The move to call Sidney
Blumenthal to testify surprises legal scholars, who view Betty
Currie, President Clinton's personal secretary, as a much more
important witness. By Ann Scales. 900 words.
</P>
