churchman and the world's most publicized sinner meet. Pope John
Paul II challenges President Clinton to seek ``a higher moral
vision.'' By Diego Ribadeneira. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   EXECUTION-YOUTH (Washington) _ On Feb. 4 the youngest person
since the reinstatement of the death penalty is to be executed in
Oklahoma. He seeks clemency in a case closely watched in Europe. By
Louise D. Palmer. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   EXERCISE-BENEFITS (Undated) _ Two studies indicate that people
who organize exercise informally get the same health benefits after
a 2-year period as people who train formally. By Richard A. Knox
and Andy Dabilis. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   BABBITT-INVADE (Cambridge, Mass.) _ Interior Secretary Bruce
Babbitt says Clinton administration will soon order federal
agencies to develop plans to reduce ``the bio-invasion'' of US
harbors by alien fauna. By Peter Howe.700 words.
</P>
