<HEADLINE>
SHOPPING ON THE WEB
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies RETAILING-INTERNET) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   As online retailing grows, traditional stores are moving to
improve their presence on the web. Here's a sampling:
</P>
<P>
   Wal-Mart (www.wal-mart.com)
</P>
<P>
   Offers 175,000-250,000 items for sale online at any given time,
compared with the 80,000-100,000 items you would find in Wal-Mart
stores and supercenters. Want a book on fishing? This Web site
offers 45. Wal-Mart also offers built-to-order computers
exclusively through its Web site, and it has an online partnership
with FTD florists. ``You're going to find many of the same items
you would find in a store, but you would find a bigger selection of
videos and books and CDs because you're not limited by a physical
store,'' spokesman Bryan Holmberg said. Wal-Mart, like most
retailers, is not believed to do a significant portion of its $100
billion-a-year-plus in revenues from the Web and does not disclose
those figures. But its market position as the world's largest
retailer and its high level of sophistication in moving merchandise
from supplier to stores make it a player to watch in online
retailing.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   J.C. Penney (www.jcpenney.com)
</P>
<P>
   Offers selected merchandise and gift certificates, as well as
access to a gift registry. This year, it will begin to debut sites
targeting specialized audiences, such as full-figured women. Wants
to have full Penney catalog available online this year.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Pier 1 Imports (www.pier1.com)
</P>
<P>
   Uses its site to sell gift certificates and provide access to a
bridal registry, will begin selling merchandise online this year.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Radio Shack (www.radioshack.com)
</P>
<P>
   Uses its site to display merchandise and provide store location
information. Will begin selling merchandise online this year.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   The Gap (www.gap.com)
</P>
<P>
   Lets customers select outfits and view them on 360-degree
rotational models, and offers a detail magnification feature.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Barnes &AMP; Noble (www.barnesandnoble.com)
</P>
<P>
   Offers more than 5.5 million books for sale and boasts online
author chats that the company says have drawn as many as 20,000
participants.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Victoria's Secret (www.victoriassecret.com)
</P>
<P>
   Valentine's alert: Will use its site for a live Webcast of its
annual fashion show at 6 p.m. CST Feb. 3.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Partnerships: J.C. Penney advertises on high-traffic sites like
America Online. Barnes &AMP; Noble is exclusive bookseller for The Walt
Disney Co. and is exclusive bookseller on nine of the top 10 news
and information web sites and 10 of the 20 most-trafficked web
sites.
</P>
<P>
   _Compiled by Lila LaHood
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
