<P>
   IMPEACH-TRIAL (Washington) _ In the chamber: Fervent arguments
from the prosecution and defense counsel on the highly divisive
question of calling witnesses in President Clinton's impeachment
trial, followed by a second straight evening of closed-door debate,
moved the Senate closer tonight to a decision to take depositions
from three of the main figures in the protracted proceeding. By
R.W. Apple Jr. (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``w''
