<P>
   POPE-U.S. (St. Louis) _ Ignoring the moral lapses of President
Clinton, Pope John Paul II flew into in St. Louis today and
addressed the broader moral failings of the nation. The Pope
referred to the infamous 1857 Dred Scott decision affirming
slavery, which was heard in St. Louis, and called it a ``a time of
testing,'' which the United States failed. ``America faces a
similar time of trial today,''the Pope said, in reference to the
abortion issue. By Alessandra Stanley. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m.
ET in ``a'' news file.) With sidebars inside.
