Kenneth Starr, a divided federal appeals panel reinstates a tax
fraud case he brought against Webster Hubbell, a longtime Arkansas
friend of President and Mrs. Clinton. The court majority said that
a lower-court judge was wrong when he threw out the caseon grounds
that the independent counsel had overreached. By Neil A. Lewis.
(Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
