for Attention Deficit Disorder and increasingly common asthma
inhalers; help medically fragile students with catheters or tube
feedings; teach children to wash their hands frequently or persuade
teen-agers to quit smoking and consider celibacy, and much, much
more. By Carey Goldberg. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a''
news file.)
