<P>
   BRAZIL-PRICES (Chicago) _ While the overall economy remains
vibrant, calculations by futures traders are an indication that the
crisis in Brazil is already reverberating in the United States _
both positively and negatively. As Brazil's currency, the real, has
dropped 30 percent in the last two weeks, the wholesale prices of a
broad range of goods have fallen, sending new shock waves through
the U.S.' grain belt and industrial heartland. By David Barboza.
</P>
