   MARKET (New York) _ Stock prices rose for a second straight
session, pushed higher by renewed interest in technology shares and
an absence of fresh bad news from financially troubled countries
like Brazil. Better than expected fourth quarter earnings reports
and stock split announcements by a number of well-established
companies provided additional stimulus, analysts and traders said.
By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
