calls attention to itself. The Eau Claire, Wis., company has the
reputation of being run more like a private company than a publicly
held one. But that is due to change, now that a group of analysts
has chosen the company as the subject of an educational project on
how small investors can benefit from shareholder activism. By
Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
