<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Going deep down the middle
 &HT;    (EDS: Graphic to accompany this blurb is available _ call CoxNet
at (404) 526-5456 if you need assistance.)
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Falcons' ``Z-post'' is similar to the pass play the Broncos
ran in the AFC title game that started their second-half comeback
against the New York Jets. Wide receiver Terance Mathis, aligned to
the left, runs a deep crossing route and hopes to influence the
coverage of Broncos free safety Steve Atwater. Flanked to the
right, wide receiver Tony Martin runs a deep post pattern. Tight
end O.J. Santiago runs a short option route in the right hook area.
The Falcons protect Chris Chandler with seven blockers.
</P>
