kindly to white-collar cowboys who break securities laws.
</P>
<P>
   Robert S. Mueller III has only been U.S. Attorney in these parts
for about six months, but already he is showing that he's a man of
his word. Not long after being appointed federal prosecutor for
Northern California, Mueller declared that he was going to make
fighting white-collar crime a priority, particularly insider
trading and high-technology-related fraud in Silicon Valley. By
columnist Mark Veverka
</P>
