   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; ENTREPRENEUR PACKAGE &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; ECOMMERCE  &LR; _ Neither Matt Glickman nor Mark Selcow had a child when
they came up with the idea three years ago of launching an online
company focused exclusively on new and expectant parents.
</P>
<P>
   But Glickman and his wife were thinking about having a baby and
Selcow was familiar with the women's health market from his job at
a bio-medical company.
</P>
<P>
   The two decided to meld editorial content and commerce and
provide comprehensive information on preconception, pregnancy and
babies as well as health education and a full line of products. By
Peter Sinton
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GROW  &LR; _ Question: Venture capital is usually hard to get
without a track record and blue chip contacts. Can you suggest ways
to find private equity financing quickly and easily, preferably
online? Columnist Peter Sinton has the answer
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
