<SLUG> BC-COSTELLO-PLEA-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Costello to admit part in murder
 &HT;    By Pat Moore
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   STUART, Fla. _ Lisa Costello will end more than 2 1/2 years of
silence today and admit her role in the 1996 murder and kidnapping
of New Jersey bus company owner Frank Black, according to a plea
agreement her attorney reached with prosecutors this week.
</P>
<P>
   A judge is scheduled to hear Costello's plea to reduced charges
that implicate her in the elaborate plot to murder her millionaire
boyfriend's business rival.
</P>
<P>
   The former Jupiter woman has agreed to testify against Alan
Mackerley as he appeals his convictions for kidnapping and
murdering Black at his Stuart waterfront home Feb. 24, 1996.
Mackerley was sentenced to life in prison after jurors found him
guilty of both charges last year.
</P>
<P>
   As part of the plea deal, Costello will admit Frank Black is
dead, that Mackerley killed him, but that she did not see Black
being killed, court records show.
</P>
<P>
   If retired Florida Supreme Court Chief Justice James Alderman
accepts the plea recommendations from prosecuting and defense
attorneys, Costello will be sentenced to 10 years in prison with
credit for the past 2 1/2 years she spent in the Martin County
Jail.
</P>
<P>
   She spent nearly two of those years jailed on a contempt charge
for refusing to tell investigators what she knew about Black's
disappearance. On the day the contempt charge expired,
investigators charged her with Black's murder and kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm looking forward to hearing what she has to say _ that's
for certain _ but it's not over until it's over,'' said Florida
Department of Law Enforcement Agent Mike Driscoll. He and retired
FBI Agent Jay Miller are scheduled to interview Costello under oath
before today's court session at the Martin County Courthouse.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators say Costello used a false name to lure Black to
Florida under the guise of conducting a business deal nearly three
years ago.
</P>
<P>
   She picked him up at Palm Beach International Airport and used
one his credit cards seven hours after his arrival.
</P>
<P>
   Mackerley shot Black at his Stuart home, then dumped his body
from his speedboat into the ocean, authorities say. Black's body
was never found.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors will give Costello a choice of pleading to several
charges, but they will recommend a 10-year prison sentence and a
15-year probation term no matter what she decides.
</P>
<P>
   With credit for good behavior in prison, she could be out in
about five years, her attorney Richard Kibbey said.
</P>
<P>
   Black's daughters, Diane and Leeanna Black, said they did not
want to comment Tuesday on the proposed plea deal.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
