<SLUG> BC-MRV-STOCK-JUMP-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MRV COMMUNICATIONS STOCK BOUNCES BACK WITH GAIN OF OVER 20 PERCENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE McNARY  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES -- Shares of telecommunications equipment specialist
MRV Communications Inc. surged more than 20 percent for their
biggest gain since the stock melted down five months ago.
</P>
<P>
   MRV rose $1.6975 to $9.875 a share Tuesday with 2.97 million
shares changing hands, or six times the 30-day average volume. The
upward spike followed an announcement of new router and switching
products for networks along with analyst Richard Berry of J.P.
Turner &AMP; Co. issuing a ``trading buy'' recommendation with a
three-to-six month target of $12 to $13.
</P>
<P>
   The run-up erased a significant chunk of the issue's Aug. 28
plunge, which saw shares fall from $14.375 to $6.8125 after MRV
announced a downbeat third-quarter forecast due to slow European
sales and delays of new products. MRV shares are still down 31
percent from the Aug. 27 close and 74 percent off the all-time high
of $38.75 in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Analyst Fredrik Tjernstrom of Emerging Growth Alert, who issued
a ``buy'' rating on the stock after the August decline, said MRV
had fallen out of favor with investors due to concerns about its
ability to produce profits after recent acquisitions.
</P>
<P>
   Tjernstrom also said it would be no surprise for MRV's stock to
keep rising due to the strong fiber-optic products in development.
</P>
<P>
   The company made the product announcements Tuesday at the Comnet
trade show in Washington, D.C. It will ship the GFS3012 switch
router, listed at $7,995, next month and the AccelRouter, listed at
$13,995 with the ability to boost network performance by as much as
100 times, in March.
</P>
<P>
   MRV's third-quarter earnings declined sharply to $1.55 million,
or 6 cents a share, from $5.92 million, or 23 cents a share, in the
same period in 1997. Sales amounted to $62.3 million, compared with
$42 million in the year-earlier period, but were down $3.4 million
from the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The company plans to report fourth-quarter earnings Feb. 16.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
