of yam teeter in a gratin at Mesa Grill. What makes this gratin so
exceptional? The precise slicing of the yams. The secret of such
perfection, the tool that no chef would live without, is the
mandoline. With this slicing tool, they can cut carrots on an angle
into exactly one-sixteenth-inch slices. (Michael Rogol/New York
Times Photo)
