</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) HAVANA -- Jan. 26, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JAN. 31 --
CUBA-HEALTH-1-COX, 1-26 -- Dr. Eliecer Suarez, left, quizzes
medical residents on a patient's condition during morning rounds at
the Ameijeiras Brothers Hospital, Havana's premier healthcare
facility. Doctors, whose average salary is $240 per month, are so
underpaid that some are contemplating leaving their fields to work
instead in the tourism industry where they can earn more from
foreigners in daily tips than they can from the government in
monthly incomes. (Rick McKay/Cox News Service)
