check the first assembly line version of the F-22 Stealth fighter
built in the Marietta plant in April 1997. Some critics suggest
that the government buy far fewer than the planned 339 aircraft.
Each F-22 is to be built by Lockheed-Martin at an estimated at $110
million. (Joe McTyre/Atlanta Journal-Constitution Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) MARIETTA, Georgia -- Jan 26, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JAN.
31 -- MILITARY-SPENDING-2-COX, 1-26 -- C-130J cargo planes under
construction at the Lockheed plant in Marietta. Lockheed defends
the use of the C-130J as ``a matter of cost-effectiveness and
