opening ceremony of the 1996 Olympics. More than two years after
the Olympic flame was extinguished in Atlanta, Olympic organizers
are set to face the most serious inquiry into their handling of the
games including whether they did anything unethical in their
successful campaign to be awarded the Olympics. (Barton
Silverman/New York Times Photo)
