<SLUG> BC-DEAD-BABY-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFFICIALS AWAIT AUTOPSY IN DEATH OF BABY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By LOIS R. SHEA AND KELLY WINGET  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CANAAN, N.H. _ A newborn baby found dead last week in the room
of her teenage mother was apparently born alive, and authorities
continue to investigate whether to bring charges against the
17-year-old mother.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps groggy from the rigors of birth, the young mother may
have wrapped the infant, placed it under the bed, and then either
fell asleep or collapsed, The Globe has learned. The baby girl was
found dead the next morning. It is not known whether the mother
realized the baby was ever alive.
</P>
<P>
   The identity of the mother, a Mascoma Valley Regional High
School student, has not been released by authorities. They
emphasize that they are still investigating the case.
</P>
<P>
   Results of an autopsy are to be released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Friends of the mother said that she either hid her pregnancy or
was unaware that she was expecting a baby.
</P>
<P>
   At 6 a.m. last Thursday, police responded to a call from a
Canaan home reporting a baby believed to be stillborn, said
Sergeant Tim Cohen of the Canaan police. Authorities said the young
woman was staying with her boyfriend's family.
</P>
<P>
   Three officers and an ambulance crew were dispatched to the
home, where the apparently full-term baby was pronounced dead at
the scene, according to Canaan Police Chief Tony Piscopo.
</P>
<P>
   The death of the child was ruled suspicious, as is done in all
cases where the cause is not immediately clear.
</P>
<P>
   New Hampshire Attorney General Philip T. McLaughlin said
authorities are ``continuing to investigate and trying to make an
assessment'' of whether the teenager knew the baby was alive when
it was born.
</P>
<P>
   McLaughlin said he does not know if the girl went to sleep after
giving birth, or simply collapsed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can tell you that the child was found by a woman in the
morning who lived there, and the circumstances of the child being
found and the condition of the child are causing us to look
carefully to see if we can determine what actually happened,''
McLaughlin said.
</P>
<P>
   Chelsie Fellows, 15, of Canaan, said the young mother had
complained of stomach pains, ``but no one really thought anything
of it because she told people she was trying to gain weight because
she was too skinny.''
</P>
<P>
   Fellows said the girl apparently kept her secret from everyone,
including her boyfriend's parents. ``I can't picture what it was
like for her,'' Fellows said.
</P>
<P>
   Friends said the girl and her mother moved north from Louisiana
five years ago, and that she has talked about wanting to become a
model. The girl had been dating her boyfriend for about a year,
friends said.
</P>
<P>
   McLaughlin said the boyfriend's family has been ``very
cooperative'' with authorities.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a young woman who appears in many respects to have
been very much on her own,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   McLaughlin said he hopes to decide later this week whether
criminal charges are appropriate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
