<HEADLINE>
BRONCOS REPORT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN LYONS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
Sharpe not shy MIAMI _ Broncos tight end Shannon Sharpe, the most
loquacious, lip-serving player in the NFL, was at his bombastic
best yesterday at Media Day.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Some Sharpe samplings:
</P>
<P>
   On trash talking: ``I think I'm labeled as a guy that talks a
lot of trash, but I normally don't say anything until someone
starts talking to me. I'm always going to have the last word. I can
assure you of that. ... As Terrell Davis is the best player in the
game, I'm the best trash talker in the game. ... People say,
`Shannon is the most quotable guy,' but when my play doesn't match
my quotes, people will stop listening to me.''
</P>
<P>
   On how much he'll enjoy this week: ``We realize that we're here
for business. If you want to go on cruises or rent Sea Doos, come
back after the game and you can do all that. You can rent a villa
on Star Island, or fly on Sly Stallone's private jet if you want.
We're here to win a football game.''
</P>
<P>
   On why his brother, ESPN analyst Sterling Sharpe, didn't talk to
the media while he was playing: ``It came about while he was in
Green Bay. He only caught 55 balls. They criticized him, said the
Packers should have drafted Anthony Miller or Michael Irvin. The
next year, \RSterling\S comes back and leads the league in
receiving and everybody was saying what a great choice. It was too
late. He was scared. He really backed off and didn't have much to
say.'' Where's the hype? When John Elway's name is mentioned on
television, radio or in newspapers, it is often precluded with ``a
leader in fourth-quarter comebacks.'' Terrell Davis' name usually
goes with ``one of four men to rush for more than 2,000 yards.''
</P>
<P>
   But nothing is mentioned besides the name of cornerback Darrien
Gordon, who doubles as the club's punt returner. And that's too
bad, Gordon said, for quiet as it has been kept, Gordon is the
all-time leading punt returner _ in terms of average per return _
in league history.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every time I line up to catch a punt I wonder why they don't
post, `Darrien Gordon, all-time leading punt returner,' '' Gordon
said. ``I don't get any pub for that, and it's a shame.''
</P>
<P>
   Gordon's regular-season punt-return average is 13.2 yards. He
has six touchdowns, including a record-tying two in one quarter. He
has averaged 9.7 yards on 17 postseason returns with no touchdowns.
Mr. Mom After the Super Bowl last year, John Elway's wife, Janet,
developed an infection after abdomen surgery. John Elway said it
was particularly tough on his four children.
</P>
<P>
   ``They were really worried because they know what cancer is,''
Elway said. ``I just had to sit down and try to explain what was
wrong with Mom, that it wasn't cancer and that she wasn't going to
leave us. My kids are 13, 11, 9 and 7, and things get going a
little wild in their minds, and so we had a little family talk and
they were a lot better after that.'' Briefly Wide receiver Willie
Green rented a convertible blue Lamborghini that is costing him
$1,500 a day. He is sharing the expense with wide receiver Marcus
Nash. Green drove the car Monday and yesterday. Nash gets it the
rest of the week.
</P>
<P>
   Safety Tyrone Braxton on dealing with the hype of Super Bowl
week: ``You've got to love this. How can you not love all these
people? You're down here in Miami and it's January. I'm from
Wisconsin. I had the convertible top down. This is great.''
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver Rod Smith on his favorite pass pattern: ``Me,
myself, I like to go deep. That way we can get off the field, and I
can catch my breath.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
