fine layer, like a piece of puff pastry. Most chefs can dazzle home
cooks with their knife skills, but even they cannot exact such
precision on sweet potatoes and apples unaided. Their secret, the
tool that no chef would live without, is the mandoline. And this
slicing tool is perfectly suited to home cooking. By Amanda Hesser.
