<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OREGON RECRUITS CHOOSE USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC has added to its recruiting class by picking
up two oral commitments from players in Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   Chad Cook, a 6-foot-5 tight end, and Troy Polamalu, a 5-11
defensive back, decided to attend USC after visiting the campus
last week.
</P>
<P>
   Polamalu is the nephew of former USC fullback Kennedy Pola,
currently an assistant coach at Washington. Polamalu chose USC over
Colorado and Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   Notre Dame was recruiting Cook until he tore the anterior
cruciate ligament in his knee in the seventh game of the season. He
caught 23 passes for 390 yards and four touchdowns. Oregon,
Washington and California were recruiting Cook as well.
</P>
<P>
   USC now has 17 commitments, and is awaiting decisions from about
10 more players, including offensive lineman Lucas MacKay (6-5,
260) of Hughson, Calif., running back Joe Weber (6-2, 210) of San
Bernardino and wide receiver Andre Johnson (6-2, 205) of Miami.
</P>
</TEXT>
